description:
The query inside the dashboard basically shows the formula the calculate IB commission
To calculate the commission, we can just follow the formula from the website, but take note that 1 lot in MT5 is 10000 instead of 100000.
Besides, we also need to take care of the currency rate. There is some special case like client tradevol indices in GBP, the commission will be calculated in GBP and then converted to the affiliate account currency. For forex pair, the commission will be calculated in base currency and then converted to the affiliate account currency.
But the numbers we get by calculating manually cannot match to numbers provided by MetaTrader is due to 2 reasons:
1) Some clients are manually tagged to an IB some period of time after registration, so his trading before that time is not counted to the IB's commission in MetaTrader system. But we could not identify those special clients in our database
2) The multiple currency rates at a different time and rounding up issue makes the numbers hard to match
name: MT5 IB Commission
